transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra, how can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Hi, I was checking on a status on an order that was sent to me.

Speaker 1: How do you identify me, name, phone number?

Speaker 2: Sure, what is your date of birth?

Speaker 1: 06-25-62.

Speaker 2: What's your name?

Speaker 1: Robert Frawley.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I do see that there's currently an order in transit.

Speaker 2: Let me see what the status of it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: I'll tell you what I'm thinking and you tell me what we can do.

Speaker 1: I got an email that they couldn't deliver it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I am taking a look.

Speaker 1: It looks like they tried to deliver it today, but they had no access to the delivery location.

Speaker 2: Therefore, they will try to re-deliver it tomorrow.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's not going to happen because the mailbox got blown away by a snowplow.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: We have to change.

Speaker 2: Okay, then what I suggest you do is give USPS a call and see if you're able to pick it up at one of their locations.

Speaker 1: Okay, here's what I was thinking.

Speaker 2: You guys just kind of sent me this 10 for 10.

Speaker 1: I don't really want to pay that higher price.

Speaker 2: Is there any way we can just do the 40 thing and you charge me the difference?

Speaker 1: So you stick at the 10 pills for $49.

Speaker 2: I know, but I never really ordered that.

Speaker 1: You guys did that.

Speaker 2: So I ordered the first 40.

Speaker 1: Well, yeah, that got lost.

Speaker 2: I never got it.

Speaker 1: So they sent me another 10 to be nice, and I didn't want the 10 that was shipped now.

Speaker 2: Can we just – what can we do?

Speaker 1: I don't want to buy 10 at a time.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so those were sent out because of your prescription.

Speaker 1: If you do not need it every month, that's totally understandable,

Speaker 2: and we can go ahead and adjust that frequency for you, or we can modify it to every three months.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I didn't order these 10.

Speaker 2: The 10 was sent as a nice gesture.

Speaker 1: The prior 10 was sent as a nice gesture because I lost the delivered batch that I got,

Speaker 2: and I never used them.

Speaker 1: So they said, I'll tell you what we'll do.

Speaker 2: We'll send you 10 free, and they did.

Speaker 1: As you see, amount paid zero.

Speaker 2: So whoever looked in there and said, oh, he wants 10.

Speaker 1: Well, I don't want 10.

Speaker 2: That's too expensive that way.

Speaker 1: I'd rather just get the 40.

Speaker 2: So what can we do?

Speaker 1: Okay, so, yeah, I mean, what I can go ahead and do is just modify any future orders

Speaker 2: and just adjust it to every three months or every four months.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, let me just see something here.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I mean, they're much cheaper when you buy the 40, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah, you can also adjust your next shipment.

Speaker 2: You can get the 40 post if you're interested in the 40.

Speaker 1: In three months?

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Okay, when would that be?

Speaker 2: Can you just tell me what that date would be?

Speaker 1: That would be April.

Speaker 2: Okay, so what's going to happen with the 10?

Speaker 1: They're not going to be able to deliver them.

Speaker 2: Oh, so the USPS?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I say, yeah, contact USPS so that you're able to pick it up at their location.

Speaker 2: Well, can I just give you the PO box that we just set up?

Speaker 1: Can you change that?

Speaker 2: Can you do it?

Speaker 1: No, because USPS has your order, so I'm not able to modify that.

Speaker 2: You have to contact USPS directly.

Speaker 1: Okay, so what if you canceled the order?

Speaker 2: Would it just go back to you guys?

Speaker 1: I cannot cancel it because it's shipped out.

Speaker 2: USPS has your order.

Speaker 1: So what you have to do is just contact USPS and pick up the package at their location, at their facility.

Speaker 2: All right, I'll try.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you for your time.

Speaker 2: Have a nice day.

Speaker 1: You're going to change it, right?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: You're booking your next one for 40 pills, right?

Speaker 2: Okay, three months, right?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Okay, thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, you're all set.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.

Speaker 1: Bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
